The paper deals with the problem of matrix completion, which is a well-studied problem in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also introduces a relation between matrix completion and sparsity, which is a common theme in data science (cs.DS). The paper proposes algorithms that are based on adaptive sampling, which is a technique used in numerical analysis (cs.NA) and signal processing (cs.SI).
